==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roister
<hw>Roist"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Probably fr. F.
<ets>rustre</ets> boor, a clown, clownish, fr. L. <ets>rustucus</ets>
rustic. See <er>Rustic</er>.]</ety> <def>To bluster; to swagger; to
bully; to be bold, noisy, vaunting, or turbulent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a <qex>roisting</qex> challenge sent amongst⟦br⟧
The dull and factious nobles of the Greeks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roister</ent>⟦br⟧

